Social Studies of Science sss.sagepub.com

    doi: 10.1177/030631286016001008 Social Studies of Science February 1986 vol. 16 no. 1 151-172

Quantitative Measures of Communication in Science: A Study of the Formal Level

    Michael H. MacRoberts 1 and
    Barbara R. MacRoberts 2

+ Author Affiliations

    1 740 Columbia, Shreveport, Louisiana 71104, USA.
    2 740 Columbia, Shreveport, Louisiana 71104, USA.

Abstract

Studies of scientific communication have relied on citation indices and bibliographies for data. We examined papers to see how much influence appears as references in bibliographies. We found that very little does.

